title: Relatos salvajes
overview: Six short stories that explore the extremities of human behavior involving people in distress.

title: Barton Fink
overview: A renowned New York playwright is enticed to California to write for the movies and discovers the hellish truth of Hollywood.

title: La règle du jeu
overview: A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

title: Crash
overview: Los Angeles citizens with vastly separate lives collide in interweaving stories of race, loss and redemption.

title: Perfetti sconosciuti
overview: Seven long-time friends get together for a dinner. When they decide to share with each other the content of every text message, email and phone call they receive, many secrets start to unveil and the equilibrium trembles.

title: C.R.A.Z.Y.
overview: A young French-Canadian, growing up in the 1960s and 1970s, struggles to reconcile his emerging homosexuality with his father's conservative values and his own Catholic beliefs.

title: Rushmore
overview: The extracurricular king of Rushmore Preparatory School is put on academic probation.

title: Short Cuts
overview: The day-to-day lives of several suburban Los Angeles residents.

title: Chung Hing sam lam
overview: Two melancholy Hong Kong policemen fall in love: one with a mysterious female underworld figure, the other with a beautiful and ethereal server at a late-night restaurant he frequents.

title: Joker
overview: In Gotham City, mentally troubled comedian Arthur Fleck is disregarded and mistreated by society. He then embarks on a downward spiral of revolution and bloody crime. This path brings him face-to-face with his alter-ego: the Joker.

title: Jab We Met
overview: A depressed wealthy businessman finds his life changing after he meets a spunky and care-free young woman.

title: Little Miss Sunshine
overview: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

title: Chhichhore
overview: A tragic incident forces Anirudh, a middle-aged man, to take a trip down memory lane and reminisce his college days along with his friends, who were labelled as losers.

title: Heat
overview: A group of professional bank robbers start to feel the heat from police when they unknowingly leave a clue at their latest heist.

title: Amarcord
overview: A series of comedic and nostalgic vignettes set in a 1930s Italian coastal town.

title: Lost in Translation
overview: A faded movie star and a neglected young woman form an unlikely bond after crossing paths in Tokyo.

title: Deliverance
overview: Intent on seeing the Cahulawassee River before it's dammed and turned into a lake, outdoor fanatic Lewis Medlock takes his friends on a canoeing trip they'll never forget into the dangerous American back-country.

title: Manhattan
overview: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.

title: Vizontele
overview: Lives of residents in a small Anatolian village change when television is introduced to them

title: Das Boot
overview: The claustrophobic world of a WWII German U-boat; boredom, filth and sheer terror.
